Sentence: Anatol Vieru (Romanian pronunciation: [anaˈtol viˈeru]; 8 June 1926 – 8 October 1998) was a Romanian-Jewish music theoretician, pedagogue, and composer.
A pupil of Aram Khachaturian, he composed seven symphonies, eight string quartets, concertos, and chamber music.
He also wrote three operas: Iona (1976), Praznicul Calicilor (1981), and Telegrame, Tema si Variatiuni (1983).
He was awarded the Herder Prize in 1986.
He was the father of pianist, writer, and mathematician Andrei Vieru.
